      { heading: "Corporate Yacht Team Building Activities", content: "Yacht team building combines the unique environment with structured activities. Popular options include: guided Istanbul trivia challenges (learn about the landmarks while competing in teams), cocktail-making competitions with the bartender, cooking challenges with the on-board chef, photography contests (best Bosphorus shot wins), problem-solving challenges themed around maritime navigation, and structured networking activities for cross-departmental mixing. The yacht environment naturally breaks down hierarchical barriers — the CEO and the newest intern share the same deck, making conversations more natural and authentic. The shared experience of sailing the Bosphorus creates team bonding that carries back to the office." , expertQuote: { text: "Özel yat kiralama, Boğaz deneyimini tamamen kişiselleştirme imkânı tanır. Rota, zamanlama ve servis tamamen misafirlerin tercihine göre şekillenir — bu esneklik başka hiçbir tur seçeneğinde yok.", author: "Burak Şahin", title: "Profesyonel Yat Kaptanı, 20 Yıllık Deneyim" }},
      { heading: "Booking for Corporate Events", content: "Corporate yacht events benefit from advance planning. Book 2–4 weeks ahead and specify: event type and objectives, guest count and composition, preferred date and time (sunset events are most impressive), catering style and dietary requirements, AV/technical needs, branding requirements, and budget range. [TURSAB](https://www.tursab.org.tr/en)-licensed MerrySails provides a detailed event proposal including timeline, menu options, setup description, and itemized pricing. Corporate invoicing with company details is available. For recurring events (quarterly team celebrations, annual client entertaining), preferred rates can be arranged. The per-person cost of a yacht corporate event often compares favorably to upscale restaurant dining while delivering a far more memorable and impactful experience. For multinational companies hosting events during major Istanbul conferences or trade shows, early booking is essential — corporate yacht demand peaks during the same weeks as major convention center events, and the most desirable sunset departure slots are often reserved months in advance by repeat corporate clients who have experienced the impact of a Bosphorus event on their business relationships." }
