        heading: "When and How to Book for the Best Experience",
        content: "Timing your Bosphorus cruise booking can make the difference between a good experience and an extraordinary one. For sunset cruises during peak season (June-August), booking 3-5 days in advance ensures you get your preferred date — same-day availability exists but often only for less desirable time slots. Shoulder season months (April-May, September-October) offer the sweet spot: pleasant weather, stunning light for photography, and easier availability. Winter cruises (November-March) are available on a reduced schedule but offer their own magic — hot drinks, fewer tourists, and moody atmospheric views. For online bookings, our website offers instant confirmation and the most competitive prices since there's no agent commission. When booking through travel agencies or hotel concierges, compare their price with the direct price — markups of 30-50% are common. The best hack: book your cruise for the second day of your Istanbul trip rather than the first. This gives you time to acclimate, check weather conditions, and reschedule if needed. We offer free date changes up to 24 hours before departure, making advance booking essentially risk-free.",
