      { heading: "Turkish Meze Spread — Classic Yacht Menu", content: "The meze spread is the most popular yacht catering choice — perfectly suited to the casual, social atmosphere of a Bosphorus cruise. A typical meze selection includes: hummus, acılı ezme (spicy tomato-walnut paste), cacık (yogurt with cucumber), sigara böreği (crispy cheese rolls), yaprak sarma (stuffed vine leaves), patlıcan salatası (smoky eggplant salad), haydari (herb yogurt dip), and fresh bread. The meze format is ideal for yacht dining because it is easy to share, does not require formal table settings, and pairs perfectly with drinks. Add grilled meat or seafood for a more substantial meal. Meze platters serve 8–15 guests and are prepared fresh before the charter." , expertQuote: { text: "Yat üzerinde ikram planlamasında taze ve yerel malzemeler ön planda olmalı. İstanbul'un zengin deniz ürünleri ve meze kültürü, tekne üstü gastronomi için mükemmel bir temel oluşturur.", author: "Deniz Aras", title: "Gastronomi Yazarı & Yat Şefi" }},
      { heading: "Yacht Catering — Seafood and BBQ Options", content: "For a heartier yacht menu, seafood and BBQ options elevate the experience. The seafood menu includes: grilled sea bass (levrek), shrimp, calamari, and octopus, served with seasonal salad and rice. Fresh fish is sourced from Istanbul's morning markets. The BBQ menu features Turkish-style grilled meats: chicken shish, lamb kebab, köfte (meatballs), and grilled vegetables, served with pilaf and salad. Both menus can be prepared by the crew on the yacht's grill or by a private chef (VIP package). For the most impressive presentation, the VIP private chef creates a tasting menu with multiple courses timed to scenic moments during the cruise." },
      { heading: "Yacht Catering Drinks — From Tea to Champagne", content: "The drink selection sets the mood for your charter. Basic (Essential): Turkish tea, coffee, and water. Premium: wine (Turkish reds and whites), beer (Efes, craft options), spirits (rakı, vodka, whisky, gin), soft drinks, juices. VIP: everything in Premium plus champagne (Moët or equivalent), premium spirits, and cocktail service. Turkish rakı — the national spirit — is a classic Bosphorus drink; served with cold water and ice, it turns milky white (earning the nickname 'lion's milk'). For celebrations, champagne towers or custom cocktails can be arranged. Non-alcoholic options are always comprehensive: fresh juices, Turkish ayran (salted yogurt drink), homemade lemonade, and premium teas." , expertQuote: { text: "İstanbul'un sokak yemekleri, şehrin binlerce yıllık kültürel birikiminin lezzet formuna dönüşmüş halidir. Simit, balık ekmek ve lahmacun — her biri bir tarihi taşır.", author: "Deniz Aras", title: "Gastronomi Yazarı & Yat Şefi" }},
      { heading: "Yacht Catering — Special Dietary Requirements", content: "All yacht catering can accommodate dietary needs. Vegetarian menus feature meze platters (naturally veggie-heavy in Turkish cuisine — recognized by the [Ministry of Culture and Tourism](https://www.kultur.gov.tr) as intangible cultural heritage —), grilled vegetable kebabs, and Turkish salads. Vegan options include hummus, rice-stuffed vegetables, grilled aubergine, and fresh fruit. Gluten-free guests can enjoy all grilled items and most meze (börek excluded). Halal food is standard — Turkish cuisine is inherently halal. Kosher arrangements can be made with advance notice. Allergies should be communicated when booking — the chef or catering team adjusts the menu accordingly. For custom dietary requirements, the VIP private chef creates a fully personalized menu around your needs. Dietary requirements are taken seriously across all catering tiers — halal preparation is standard on all Turkish menu items, vegetarian and vegan menus are fully developed alternatives rather than afterthoughts, and allergen-free options including gluten-free and nut-free are available with 48 hours advance notice, ensuring every guest aboard can enjoy the dining experience fully." }
