      { q: "How many guests can a yacht party accommodate?", a: "Depending on the vessel, yacht parties accommodate 5 to 80 guests. Standard yachts handle 5–15 guests, mid-range vessels suit 15–40, and luxury yachts accommodate 40–80. Guest count must not exceed the vessel's maritime certification limit." },
      { q: "Can we bring our own food and drinks to a yacht party?", a: "Most licensed operators prefer to handle catering for food safety and insurance reasons. However, you can typically bring a special cake, specific wine bottles, or personal items. Discuss any outside provisions during the booking process." },
      { q: "How far in advance should I book a yacht party in Istanbul?", a: "For peak season (May–September) Saturday evenings, book 3–4 weeks ahead. Weekday bookings need 1–2 weeks. Off-season bookings can often be arranged within a few days. Holiday weekends and New Year's Eve sell out months in advance." },
      { q: "What happens if it rains on our yacht party date?", a: "Light rain does not cancel the party — all yachts have enclosed areas with panoramic windows. In genuinely unsafe weather, the operator reschedules free of charge. The Bosphorus is a sheltered strait, so severe weather cancellations average fewer than 8 per year." },
      { q: "Can we have a DJ and dancing on the yacht?", a: "Yes. Mid-range and luxury yachts support professional DJ setups with marine-grade speakers and LED lighting. Stern deck areas on larger vessels provide dedicated dance floors. DJ hire starts from €200 for a 3-hour set." }
