        heading: "How to Book a Private Yacht in Istanbul — Step by Step",
        content: "Booking a private yacht in Istanbul is straightforward when you work with a licensed operator. Here is the process from inquiry to boarding. Step one: determine your requirements. Decide your group size, preferred date and time, event type, and budget range. This information allows the operator to recommend the right vessel and package immediately. Step two: contact the operator directly. Use WhatsApp, phone, or the website booking form. Avoid street agents and unlicensed intermediaries — they add commissions without adding value. For MerrySails, WhatsApp (+90 537 040 68 22) provides the fastest response, typically within 1-2 hours. Step three: review the proposal. The operator will provide vessel options, package details, pricing, and available dates. Ask for vessel photos and specifications. Confirm that the operator holds a valid <a href='https://www.tursab.org.tr/en' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>TURSAB</a> licence — this is your guarantee of consumer protection, proper insurance, and regulatory compliance. Step four: confirm with a deposit. Most operators require a 30-50% deposit to secure the booking, with the balance due on the day of charter. Payment is typically accepted via credit card, bank transfer, or cash in EUR, USD, or TRY. Step five: pre-charter coordination. Discuss your route preferences, music playlist, any special requirements (dietary restrictions, surprise elements, decoration specifics), and arrival logistics with the crew. Step six: arrive at the marina 15-20 minutes before departure. The captain briefs you on safety procedures, confirms the route, and you are underway. Free cancellation is typically available up to 24 hours before departure for a full refund. Date changes are accommodated with the same flexibility. Weather-related cancellations are rescheduled at no cost.",
